Distribution. Japan , Korea , China , Taiwan , and Vietnam (cf.
Table 1
).

Remarks.
Uca arcuata
is widely distributed in continental East Asia ( Korea , China , and Vietnam ), East Asian islands ( Japan , including the Ryukyus, Taiwan , and Penghu), and Hainan (cf.
Table 1
;
Kamita 1941
;
Dai et al. 1986
;
Dai & Yang 1991
;
Shih 1994
;
Kosuge et al. 1997
;
Yoshigou 2001
;
Shih et al. 2008
). It is probably one of the most common species in East Asia , especially on mudflats associated with mangroves (cf.
Shih et al. 1999
). In China , this species has been recorded from southern Shandong to Guangxi and northern Hainan (
Table 1
).
